docs {
  # Activate Graph Version

  Promote an inactive version to active. The currently active version (if any) is demoted to inactive atomically.

  ## Path Parameters
  - `id`: Graph UUID
  - `version_id`: Version UUID to activate

  ## Business Rules
  - Only **inactive** versions can be activated
  - Draft and already-active versions are rejected with 400
  - The swap is atomic: the old active version becomes inactive and the target version becomes active in a single transaction
  - Only one active version is allowed per graph at any time

  ## Response (Success)
  ```json
  {
    "status": true,
    "result": {
      "id": "version-uuid",
      "version_number": 2,
      "status": "active",
      "tags": [],
      "commit_message": "Initial release",
      "created_at": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
      "nodes": [...],
      "edges": [...]
    }
  }
  ```

  ## Response (Error - Not Inactive)
  ```json
  {
    "status": false,
    "result": "Only inactive versions can be activated."
  }
  ```

  ## Response (Error - Version Not Found)
  ```json
  {
    "status": false,
    "result": "Version not found."
  }
  ```

  ## Response (Error - Duplicate Exposed Output Port Display Names)
  ```json
  {
    "status": false,
    "result": "Duplicate exposed output port display name 'response' found on nodes 'LLM 1' and 'LLM 2'. All exposed output port display names must be unique for activation."
  }
  ```
  This error occurs when two or more unconnected output ports across the version share the same `display_name`. To fix, give each exposed output port a unique `display_name`. Note: duplicate input port display_names are allowed (broadcast pattern).

  ## Side Effects
  - Dataset columns are synced (add-only) for the new active version's exposed input ports. Columns are never deleted — previously created columns from other versions remain in the dataset.

  ## Atomicity
  The entire operation is wrapped in a database transaction. If any error occurs, all changes are rolled back — the old active version remains active and the target version remains inactive.
}
